article.headline: Maine 64, Dartmouth 55
article.story: PORTLAND, Maine (AP) -- Led By Ernest Turner's game-high 21 points and five steals, Maine beat Dartmouth 64-55 Tuesday night. After trading the lead for much of the first half, Maine (3-6) took control at halftime and shut down Dartmouth (1-3). Dartmouth went on a 7-0 run to start the game but Turner fueled a late first half run that gave Maine a 30-27 lead at the break. Rashard Turner had 16 points for Maine. Maine hauled in 27 rebounds, blocked four shots and had just 11 turnovers. Dartmouth got 12 points from Mike Lang and had 16 team turnovers.
